# Install Engine (Phase 17)

Read **[INSTALL_ENGINE.md](../../INSTALL_ENGINE.md)** before installation, onboarding, domain, connection, or embedded runtime work.

## Layer placement

| Concern | Layer | Paths |
|---------|-------|-------|
| Global templates & metrics | Platform | `app/platform/install-engine/`, `app/platform/installations/` |
| Wizard, connections, learning | Customer | `app/app/`, `components/app/install-engine/` |
| Heartbeat, discovery, context scan | Embedded | `app/api/install/`, `lib/embed/`, `lib/install/` |

## Rules

1. Reuse `lib/install/` constants — do not duplicate workflow steps, business types, or heartbeat statuses
2. Plan limits via `getPlanInstallLimits()` / `lib/core/plans.ts` — never hardcode tier caps
3. Human validation required before activating discovered capabilities (approve · modify · reject)
4. Learning phase defaults to 30 days — no aggressive automation during supervised learning
5. Skill recommendations must reference registered skill IDs from `lib/core/skills/registry.ts`
6. Tenant isolation mandatory; only verified domains may activate installations

> Installing Aipify should feel like onboarding an operations assistant — not configuring complicated software.
